1) WAP to check if number is divisible by 5 or not.

public class Example {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int x=5;
        if(x%5==0)
            System.out.println(x+" is divisible by 5");
        else
            System.out.println(x+" is not divisible by 5");
    }
}

2) WAP to check if number is even or odd.

public class Example {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int x=5;
        if(x%2==0)
            System.out.println(x+" is even");
        else
            System.out.println(x+" is odd");
    }
}

3) WAP to check if number is even or odd without using modulo operator.

public class Example {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int x=2;
        if((x&1)==1)
            System.out.println(x+" is odd");
        else
            System.out.println(x+" is even");
    }
}

4) WAP to check whether a number is positive or non-positive.

public class Example {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int x=0;
        if(x>0)
            System.out.println(x+" is positive");
        else
            System.out.println(x+" is non-positive");
    }
}

5) WAP to print greater between two numbers.

public class Example {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int a=20,b=34;
        System.out.println((a>b?a:b)+" is greater");
    }
}

6) WAP to check whether a given number is positive, negative or zero.

public class Example {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int x=5;
        if(x>0)
            System.out.println(x+" is positive");
        else if(x<0)
            System.out.println(x+" is negative");
        else
            System.out.println(x+" is zero");
    }
}

